# CRM platform evolution

Read `docs/CRM_PLATFORM_BLUEPRINT.md` before building any CRM, Marketing, Sales, Automation, or Analytics feature.

## Non-negotiables

- **Extend** Vite/React + Vercel serverless + existing store — do not greenfield Next.js/NestJS/K8s unless the user explicitly requests a stack migration.
- **Unified platform** — new features must share workspace scoping, timeline events, permissions patterns, and navigation (`navConfig.js`).
- **Original design** — HubSpot/Attio/Linear/Notion/Stripe-level polish; never copy their assets or layouts.

## Shell UX

- Left nav · top command bar · `LeadWorkspace` record pattern · no full page reloads.
- Global **⌘K / Ctrl+K** command palette (`CommandPalette.jsx`, `/api/platform/search`).
- Prefer `platform-design-system.css` tokens for new UI.

## Objects

Pipeline `savedLeads` is the hub. Promote Companies/Deals/Contacts as views without breaking lead-centric APIs.

## Automations

Reuse marketing graph runner + `AutomationCanvas` patterns for CRM workflows. Wire triggers to pipeline save, deal status, marketing events.

## Before shipping

Run `npm run prod:ship`. Do not commit Android/Capacitor unless deploy scope includes mobile.

## CRM activity attribution (all orgs)

When building rep/team metrics, **Last active** must mean the latest CRM action **performed by that user** (`actor_id` / strict `createdByUserId`). Never use lead assignee, workspace pulse, or login alone for that column.

- **Period filters:** use `canonicalActivityPeriod` — `day` | `7d` | `30d` (map `week`→`7d`, `month`→`30d`; never mix calendar week with rolling 7d).
- **Rep review / scoped rep:** one scope via `buildRepReviewPayload` or `readActivityLogCached` + `overlayScopedMemberIntelligence` — rollup and activity feed must share the same `since`/`until` and actor filter.
- **Last active (CRM):** `resolveLastCrmActivityMap` — SQL per-actor + org activity-log entry scan.
- **In-app time:** `aggregateWorkspaceUsage().lastInAppAt` — separate from CRM last active.
- Never scope activity scans by lead assignee only when reporting rep work (reps log on any lead they touch).
